Width and Height
width: Defines how wide an element is. Can use units like pixels (px), percentages (%).

height: Defines the height of an element using similar units.

 Background Image Properties
background-image: Sets an image to be used as the background of an element.

background-repeat: Controls whether and how the background image is repeated (horizontally, vertically, or not at all).

background-size: Determines how the background image should be scaled (can be a specific size, or scaled to cover or contain the element).

background-position: Positions the background image inside the container.

background-attachment: Specifies whether the background scrolls with the page or stays fixed.

 Border Properties
border: A shorthand for setting border width, style, and color.

border-style: Defines the style of the border (solid, dashed, dotted, double, none, etc.).

border-width: Specifies the thickness of the border.

border-color: Sets the color of the border.

border-radius: Rounds the corners of an element. we can apply it to one or more corners.

 Margin and Padding
margin: Controls the space outside an element. Can set individual sides or use shorthand values.

padding: Controls the space inside an element between the content and the border.

 Color and Background Color
color: Sets the color of the text.

background-color: Sets the background color of an element.

 Font and Text
font-size: Adjusts the size of the text.

text-align: Aligns the text inside an element (left, center, right, justify).

 CSS Selectors
ID Selector: Targets a specific element with a unique identifier.

Class Selector: Targets one or more elements with a shared class name.

Element Selector: Targets all instances of a specific HTML element (like h1, p, etc.).

 CSS Styling Methods
Inline CSS: Style written directly inside the HTML element using the style attribute.

Internal CSS: Style written within a <style> tag inside the <head> section of the HTML file.

External CSS: Styles are written in a separate CSS file and linked to the HTML file using the <link> tag.

